                  <list>
                    <item>
                      <p>Vellum, about 9 1/2 in. by 6 5/8, consisting of 56 leaves, some of which
                        are much stained and torn, especially foll. 1, 2, 8, and 56. The quires,
                        signed with letters, are 7 in number, but the first is imperfect, a leaf
                        being lost at the beginning and another after fol. 6. Each page is divided
                        into two columns, of from 25 to 31 lines. This volume is written in a good,
                        regular hand of the ixth cent.</p>
                    </item>
